tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured values are within or close to normal ranges, except for a mildly decreased hematocrit and a slightly elevated platelet distribution width. These findings may suggest mild anemia and some platelet size variability, but are not clinically alarming in isolation. No evidence of acute metabolic, renal, or hematologic derangement. Recommend clinical correlation and follow-up if symptoms or risk factors are present.
